    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Turn the grill on to medium-high and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a <strong>tin foil </strong>lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until blistered</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mafaldine-pasta-fagioli-with-cannellini-beans-and-cavolo-nero/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot (with a matching lid) over a medium heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> panko breadcrumbs </strong>with the<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 2-3 min or until golden, stirring frequently</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mafaldine-pasta-fagioli-with-cannellini-beans-and-cavolo-nero/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> and <strong>red wine paste</strong> in 280ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[350ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[470ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mafaldine-pasta-fagioli-with-cannellini-beans-and-cavolo-nero/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the panko is golden, transfer it to a small bowl and mix through <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli cheese</strong> <strong>pangrattato</strong></p><p>Return the pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mafaldine-pasta-fagioli-with-cannellini-beans-and-cavolo-nero/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>blistered tomatoes</strong> and give everything a good mix up, then cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>stock</strong> and your <strong>cannellini beans</strong> (no need to drain!) with all the <strong>bean water</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p><p>Wash, then chop your<strong> cavolo nero</strong> roughly, removing any tough stalks</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mafaldine-pasta-fagioli-with-cannellini-beans-and-cavolo-nero/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a separate pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for an initial 5-6 min (7\u20138 min for wholewheat) or until almost cooked</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta, reserving 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[60ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml] </span>of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mafaldine-pasta-fagioli-with-cannellini-beans-and-cavolo-nero/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly thickened, use a <strong>stick blender</strong> to roughly blitz into a sauce</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped cavolo nero</strong> with a little <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until wilted</p><p>Stir through the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> with the <strong>drained pasta</strong> and a large pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for a further 2-3 min</p><p>Season with a small pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>mafaldine pasta fagioli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mafaldine-pasta-fagioli-with-cannellini-beans-and-cavolo-nero/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mafaldine pasta fagioli</strong> in a bowl topped with the <strong>chilli cheese pangratatto</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>mafaldine pasta fagioli with cannellini beans & cavolo nero</strong></p><p>Add a large drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
